    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 assessment plan. Primary QoI (RHI) predictions fall within experimental scatter at four of five operating points, meeting the RH < 1 acceptance criterion for worst-case identification. Model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Note: aleatory variability in hemolysis measurements was characterized qualitatively for the RHI and wall shear stress validation results; structured probabilistic UQ was completed for pressure head, velocity field, and torque QoIs.",
